      "comment": "Debutant POINT THE WAY (5) is a fascinating subject here, getting to the races after a few impressive trial performances, but the latest of them was back on March 16. That's some sort of query, but in that latest jumpout he finished fourth but went to the line with plenty in hand. The one prior he was a dominant on-speed winner. A winning debut would not shock. BLACKJACK (1) has always carried a bit of a boom and had his first start since changing stables on the Ballarat syntho on Jun 26 when he was a respectable third, albeit beaten four lengths. He'll be better for that and looks a key player again. BOLD JESTER (2) is from a camp whose horses improve with racing, so expect a peak performance after a couple of adequate performances to start the career. IMPENDING FURY (4) has changed camps since his latest appearance and a couple of nice trials hint at an improved showing. FRAM STRAIT (3) is an ex-Godolphin gelding who has the talent to win.",
